<h1 id="activity_cards">Activity Cards</h1>

<span><p>
Activity cards present simple scripts to help users get started with an activity.
They are designed to be printed two per page and folded in half to make a two-sided card.
To make them last longer, the cards can be laminated or printed on card stock.
</p></span>

<p><span><img src="Activity_Cards.jpg" width="250" alt="Activity_Cards.jpg"></span></p>

<h2>Easy Activity Cards: micro:bit</h2>

<span><p>
These cards help students get started with the micro:bit.
They are ideal for younger students or anyone just getting started with the micro:bit.
No additional components are needed except where noted.
</p></span>

<ul class="list">
    <li><a href="cards/mb_Getting_Started.pdf">Getting Started</a> - <small><a href="cards/DE/mb_Getting_Started_DE.pdf">German version</a></small></li>
    <li><a href="cards/mb_Sensors.pdf">Sensors</a></li>
    <li><a href="cards/mb_Sounds.pdf">Sounds</a></li>
    <li><a href="cards/mb_Step_Counter.pdf">Step Counter</a></li>
    <li><a href="cards/mb_Battery_Tester.pdf">Battery Tester</a></li>
    <li><a href="cards/mb_Radio.pdf">Radio</a></li>
    <li><a href="cards/mb_NeoPixels.pdf">NeoPixels</a> (requires NeoPixels)</li>
    <li><a href="cards/mb_Servos.pdf">Servos</a> (requires a servo and a way to connect it)</li>
    <li><a href="cards/mb_IR_Remote_Control.pdf">IR Remote Control </a> (requires an IR receiver and an IR remote control)</li>
</ul>

